result.execSummary:
Jody B Rice was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jody B Rice was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 09:32 AM Defendant Jody B Rice in court, in custody.  Gilbert Grant Thompson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. This is extradition hearing - to State of Texas; Atty. Thompson heard - Def. has spoken to SPD, waived their services and will waive extradition; Court reviews right to counsel; Def. wishes to proceed and go to Texas asap; State heard, Def. should be picked up by Texas w/in next 2 weeks; Court reviews rights; Court reviews charge and finds PC; Court reviews Waiver; Def. signs same; Court signs Order for Extradition; copies given to DA to distribute; Court will tickle for 10 days to make sure Def. has been picked up by Texas
